{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775838863171,"sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","part":{"id":"prt_d783e9f42001DxTL9qbpKva030","messageID":"msg_d783e9823001GxN5sQhvr7vJkH","sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775838864678,"sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","part":{"id":"prt_d783ea2c1001zC47O3IXPMEn68","messageID":"msg_d783e9823001GxN5sQhvr7vJkH","sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the OpenSpec format. Let me write the `delta-spec.md` for AR-001:","time":{"start":1775838864675,"end":1775838864675}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838909169,"sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","part":{"id":"prt_d783ea524001xPTUNg6zvy4nER","messageID":"msg_d783e9823001GxN5sQhvr7vJkH","sessionID":"ses_287c1bf30ffeD86ZPXYChE8YFH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_81cdba5c76984639ae31ec5a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD type implementations including Go API types, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeSpec` types. `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL include `sandboxImage` (string), `tools` ([]Tool), `resources` (ResourceRequirements), `timeout` (metav1.Duration), and `securityContext` (SecurityContext). `AgentRuntime` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&AgentRuntime{}, &AgentRuntimeList{})` is called during init\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntime` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec with sandbox image\n\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` YAML with `spec.sandboxImage: \"volcano.sh/agent-sandbox:latest\"`\n- **WHEN** the object is parsed by the scheme\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntime.Spec.SandboxImage` SHALL be populated with the image string\n\n#### Scenario: Tool configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.tools` contains entries with `name`, `command`, and `args`\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is deserialized\n- **THEN** each tool SHALL have `Name` (string), `Command` ([]string), and `Args` ([]string) populated\n\n#### Scenario: Resource requirements\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.resources` specifies `requests` and `limits` for CPU/memory\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is validated by the scheme\n- **THEN** `Resources` SHALL be of type `corev1.ResourceRequirements` and pass Kubernetes validation\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime status subresource\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with `Phase` (string), `Conditions` ([]metav1.Condition), `SandboxRef` (*corev1.ObjectReference), and `LastTransitionTime` (metav1.Time). `AgentRuntime` SHALL expose `.status` via the status subresource.\n\n#### Scenario: Status phase transitions\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `status.phase = \"Pending\"`\n- **WHEN** the controller updates status to `\"Running\"`\n- **THEN** `LastTransitionTime` SHALL be updated and a new Condition added to `Conditions`\n\n#### Scenario: Condition management\n\n- **GIVEN** a condition of type `\"Ready\"` with `status: \"True\"`, `reason: \"SandboxReady\"`, `message: \"Sandbox is running\"`\n- **WHEN** status is updated via the status subresource\n- **THEN** the condition SHALL be upserted into `status.conditions` with `lastTransitionTime` set\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox reference\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod is created for this AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** the controller sets `status.sandboxRef` to the pod's ObjectReference\n- **THEN** `sandboxRef` SHALL contain `name`, `namespace`, `uid`, and `apiVersion` of the sandbox\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), and `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy).\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL reference an AgentRuntime named `python-3.11` in the same namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Execution policy\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.executionPolicy` with `timeout: \"30s\"` and `maxMemory: \"512Mi\"`\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n- **THEN** `ExecutionPolicy.Timeout` and `ExecutionPolicy.MaxMemory` SHALL be populated\n\n### Requirement: CRD manifests generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` and `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` via `make gen-crd` using controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD with status subresource\n\n- **GIVEN** `+genclient` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers on `AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** `make gen-crd` runs controller-gen\n- **THEN** the CRD manifest SHALL include `spec.subresources.status: {}`\n\n#### Scenario: CRD schema validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` markers on spec fields\n- **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n- **THEN** the OpenAPI v3 schema SHALL mark those fields as required and specify types\n\n#### Scenario: CRD group and version\n\n- **GIVEN** `SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n- **WHEN** CRDs render\n- **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `spec.group = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n\n### Requirement: client-go typed client generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate typed clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/` with `AgentRuntimeInterface` providing CRUD operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime via typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `Clientset` and valid `AgentRuntime` object\n- **WHEN** `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be created via the K8s API and returned with populated metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Update status via typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with a mutable status\n- **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, ar, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** only the status subresource SHALL be updated\n\n#### Scenario: List with label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes with labels `app=sandbox` in namespace `default`\n- **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=sandbox\"})` is called\n- **THEN** only matching AgentRuntimes SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: Watch for changes\n\n- **GIVEN** a watch on `AgentRuntimes(\"default\")`\n- **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created or updated\n- **THEN** the watch channel SHALL receive an `Event` with `Type` and `Object`\n\n### Requirement: Informer factory generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate `SharedInformerFactory` under `client-go/informers/externalversions/` with `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` accessors.\n\n#### Scenario: Start informer for AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **WHEN** `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called and `factory.Start(stopCh)` runs\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL list-watch `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and populate its cache\n\n#### Scenario: Event handlers\n\n- **GIVEN** an informer with `AddEventHandler` registered\n- **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created\n- **THEN** the `OnAdd` callback SHALL be invoked with the new object\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace-filtered informer\n\n- **GIVEN** `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` with namespace `production`\n- **WHEN** the factory starts\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL only watch AgentRuntimes in `production` namespace\n\n### Requirement: Lister generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate `AgentRuntimeLister` and `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` under `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/` with `List(selector)` and `Get(name)` methods.\n\n#### Scenario: List all AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a populated informer cache\n- **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n- **THEN** all AgentRuntimes SHALL be returned from the cache\n\n#### Scenario: Get by name and namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `sandbox-1` in namespace `default` exists in cache\n- **WHEN** `lister.AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(\"sandbox-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be returned or `NotFound` error if absent\n\n### Requirement: Fake clients for testing\n\nThe system SHALL generate fake clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/` and `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/` implementing the typed interfaces.\n\n#### Scenario: Unit test with fake client\n\n- **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset()` is called\n- **WHEN** `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, `Delete` are called on the fake client\n- **THEN** operations SHALL succeed in-memory without contacting K8s API\n\n#### Scenario: Reactor for error injection\n\n- **GIVEN** a fake client with `PrependReactor(\"create\", \"agentruntimes\", ...)` that returns an error\n- **WHEN** `Create` is called\n- **THEN** the reactor SHALL intercept and return the injected error\n\n### Requirement: Scheme and codec registration\n\nThe system SHALL register types in `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` with `AddToScheme` functions for the generated client.\n\n#### Scenario: Scheme registration at client init\n\n- **GIVEN** the `client-go` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `scheme.AddToScheme(runtimeScheme)` is called\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types SHALL be recognizable by the scheme\n\n#### Scenario: Negotiated serializer\n\n- **GIVEN** a REST client with `NegotiatedSerializer`\n- **WHEN** encoding/decoding is needed\n- **THEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` SHALL be supported with `application/json`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775838909157,"end":1775838909166}}}}
